      <hedline>
        <hl1>Central Islip Courthouse Upholds Dignity</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Spector Group architect Michael Spector opposes September 17 article in which Hauppauge resident criticized design of new federal courthouse (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In ''For Central Islip, A Renaissance,'' [Sept. 17] a Hauppauge resident was quoted as criticizing the design of the new federal courthouse for not being ''warm and fuzzy.'' As a co-architect of the building, I can assure the critic that it was designed to express the dignity and the authority of the federal government. When one is called to appear before a federal judge, it would be most inappropriate to expect to enter an environment that is ''warm and fuzzy.''</p>
        <p>MICHAEL HARRIS SPECTOR  Spector Group  North Hills</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
